{% comment %}
  Required params:
  frame_height_class - css class to control frame height
  parallax_boolean - Boolean value to turn on parallax
  img_object - Image object to use used

  Example:
  {% render 'hero', img_object: section.settings.image, frame_height_class: section.settings.image_height %}
{% endcomment %}

{%- liquid
  assign default_image = 'blank.svg' | asset_url
  assign height = frame_height_class | default: 'image_height'
  assign image = img_object | default: default_image
  assign aspect_ratio = image.aspect_ratio | default: 1 
  assign modifier = modifier | default: ''
-%}
  
<div class="image__hero__frame fade-in-child {{ height }} {{ modifier }}"
  data-overflow-background
  {% if height == 'use_image' %}
    style="padding-top: {{ 1 | divided_by: aspect_ratio | times: 100 }}%;
            background-image: url('{{ image | image_url: width: 1, height: 1 }}');"
  {% endif %}
  {% if settings.parallax_enable %}data-parallax-wrapper{% endif %}>

  <div class="image__hero__pane">
    <div class="image__hero__scale"
    {% if settings.parallax_enable %}
        style="height: {{  1 | divided_by: aspect_ratio | times: 100 }}vw;"
        data-parallax-img
    {% endif %}>
      {%- comment -%}
        Native <img loading="lazy"> (or eager when caller opts in)
        instead of the legacy <div class="lazyload" data-bgset>
        background pattern. Object-fit:cover preserves the prior
        background-size:cover behavior. bg_position becomes
        object-position so per-instance crops still work.

        Caller can pass `eager: true` to upgrade an above-the-fold
        hero to loading=eager + fetchpriority=high (LCP candidate).
        Default is lazy to match the previous lazysizes behavior.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- assign img_loading = 'lazy' -%}
      {%- if eager -%}
        {%- assign img_loading = 'eager' -%}
      {%- endif -%}
      {%- comment -%}
        Hot fix 2026-04-26: removed `background-size-cover` from the
        img class. Same root cause as image-fill.liquid — the CSS rule
        `.fade-in-child .background-size-cover` sets opacity:0 by
        default and only flips to opacity:1 when lazysizes adds the
        `.lazyloaded` class. Native <img loading="lazy"> never gets
        that class. `object-fit:cover` is already applied inline.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- comment -%}
        WebP rollout 2026-04-29 (Task 5 batch). Same <picture>+<source>
        pattern shipped earlier for image-fill.liquid (commit e946c02)
        and product-grid-item-branded.liquid (commit f6761d6). Hero
        images used by section heroes (collection page, blog page,
        article page banners) — typically 1400–2400px wide, 200–500 KB
        per image at JPEG. WebP variants are 30–50% smaller, with
        meaningful network savings on mobile cellular.

        `image` here is an Image object (assigned from img_object on
        line 14), so `image_url` with format param works correctly.
        Modern browsers (~98% of HairMNL traffic per CrUX) negotiate
        the WebP via the source's type attribute. The <img> below stays
        as fallback for the few browsers that don't accept image/webp,
        and so width/height/loading/fetchpriority/alt/style continue to
        live on <img> per HTML spec (those don't go on <source>).
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <picture>
        <source type="image/webp"
                srcset="{% if image.width > 540 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 540, format: 'webp' }} 540w,{% endif %}
                        {% if image.width > 900 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 900, format: 'webp' }} 900w,{% endif %}
                        {% if image.width > 1400 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 1400, format: 'webp' }} 1400w,{% endif %}
                        {% if image.width > 1800 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 1800, format: 'webp' }} 1800w,{% endif %}
                        {% if image.width > 2400 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 2400, format: 'webp' }} 2400w,{% endif %}"
                sizes="100vw">
        <img
          class=""
          srcset="{% if image.width > 540 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 540 }} 540w,{% endif %}
                  {% if image.width > 900 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 900 }} 900w,{% endif %}
                  {% if image.width > 1400 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 1400 }} 1400w,{% endif %}
                  {% if image.width > 1800 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 1800 }} 1800w,{% endif %}
                  {% if image.width > 2400 %}{{ image | image_url: width: 2400 }} 2400w,{% endif %}
                  {{ image | image_url: 'master' }} {{ image.width }}w"
          sizes="100vw"
          src="{{ image | image_url: 'master' }}"
          width="{{ image.width }}"
          height="{{ image.height }}"
          loading="{{ img_loading }}"
          {% if eager %}fetchpriority="high"{% endif %}
          alt="{{ image.alt | strip_html | escape }}"
          style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:{{ bg_position | replace: '-', ' ' }};">
      </picture>
    </div>
  </div>

  <noscript>
    <img src="{{ image | image_url: width: 720 }}" alt="{{ image.alt | strip_html | escape }}" class="responsive-wide-image"/>
  </noscript>
</div>
  